{"cursor":"3439","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{multiple issues|\n\n\n\n}}\n\n{{Infobox organization |name = International Press Academy |image =\n|image_border = |size =  |alt = \n|caption = |abbreviation = IPA |motto = |formation = |extinction =  |type = Professional entertainment media association\n|status =  |purpose = Honor artistic\nexcellence in the areas of motion pictures, television, radio and new media\n|headquarters = Beverly Hills, California, USA |location = |coords =  |region_served =\n|membership = |leader_title = President |leader_name = Mirjana Van Blaricom\n|main_organ =  |affiliations =\n |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website =\nhttp://pressacademy.com/ |remarks = }} The 'International Press Academy' ('IPA')\nis an association of professional entertainment journalists, representing both\ndomestic and foreign markets in print, television, radio, cable and new media\noutlets. [http://www.pressacademy.com/about/ \"About the IPA\"], webpage of\nthe International Press Academy (Retrieved December 21, 2012) The academy\nwas founded in 1996 by Mirjana Van Blaricom. All full-time entertainment\njournalists are eligible to join; membership is open to journalists listed in\nthe MPAA directory and to those working journalists who submit at least six entertainment-\nrelated clips to be considered by the\nboard. [http://www.variety.com/awardcentral_article/VR1117952672.html\n\"Charting award organizations (part I): A guide to the guilds, academies,\ninstitutes and associations behind the trophies\"], webpage of ''Variety''\nmagazine retrieved April 14, 2008.\n\nThe IPA annually recognizes achievements in the fields of cinema, television and\nnew media through the Satellite Awards (originally known as the Golden Satellite\nAwards). These awards are covered by entertainment industry journals such as\n[[The Hollywood Reporter]] and [[Variety\n(magazine)|Variety]].\n\nSpecial achievement awards presented by the IPA include the Mary Pickford Award\n(for outstanding contribution to the entertainment industry), the Auteur Award\n(to honor filmmakers whose vision and artistic control are reflected in their\nfilms), and the Nikola Tesla Award (in recognition of visionary achievements in\nfilmmaking technology).\n","linknr":197,"url":"International_Press_Academy","recorded":1375068866,"links":["/w/index.php?title=International_Press_Academy&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=International_Press_Academy&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=International_Press_Academy&action=edit","/wiki/Talk:International_Press_Academy","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:Notability_(organizations_and_companies)","/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources","/wiki/Wikipedia:Merge","/wiki/Wikipedia:Redirect","/wiki/Wikipedia:Deletion_policy","http://www.google.com/search?as_eq=wikipedia&q=%22International+Press+Academy%22&num=50","http://www.google.com/search?q=%22International+Press+Academy%22&tbm=nws&tbs=ar:1","http://www.google.com/search?tbs=bks:1&q=%22International+Press+Academy%22","http://scholar.google